        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 5:06PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Conner, or 18 miles south of Hamilton, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.  Brief heavy
rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Darby, Conner, Sula, Charlos Heights, and Como.

This includes Highway 93 S between mile markers 8 and 40.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
